{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779167862507,"sessionID":"ses_1c15753b5ffe0uF0tU9Lf0PCIg","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"glob","callID":"call_03_fbVjtrQqwxv7oEXcmH6C5822","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":".claude/nestjs/guides/database-patterns.md"},"output":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/nestjs/guides/database-patterns.md","metadata":{"count":1,"truncated":false},"title":"","time":{"start":1779167862059,"end":1779167862506}},"id":"prt_e3eab19d7001cnf99pOlilEQAg","sessionID":"ses_1c15753b5ffe0uF0tU9Lf0PCIg","messageID":"msg_e3eaaf09b001sH1OBJ2m3ns5yE"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1779167862686,"sessionID":"ses_1c15753b5ffe0uF0tU9Lf0PCIg","part":{"id":"prt_e3eab1f9d001NBl6epb16ITiZA","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"7a789eab2d7c2b6f92b85ff0301f7eab1e9a5709","messageID":"msg_e3eaaf09b001sH1OBJ2m3ns5yE","sessionID":"ses_1c15753b5ffe0uF0tU9Lf0PCIg","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":19416,"input":1573,"output":227,"reasoning":80,"cache":{"write":0,"read":17536}},"cost":0.004059652}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1779167864328,"sessionID":"ses_1c15753b5ffe0uF0tU9Lf0PCIg","part":{"id":"prt_e3eab2606001HIsow9jvNM2Lga","messageID":"msg_e3eab1fed00113CRmmJPq6bE3e","sessionID":"ses_1c15753b5ffe0uF0tU9Lf0PCIg","snapshot":"4aa948622ccb50a2e1c4cd6c12e02bb8de1e7d06","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779167869259,"sessionID":"ses_1c15753b5ffe0uF0tU9Lf0PCIg","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_00_o2w0ysbhSbAgtYdSsqga1740","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/nestjs/guides/database-patterns.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/nestjs/guides/database-patterns.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Database Patterns - TypeORM in NestJS\n2: \n3: Complete guide to database access patterns using TypeORM with PostgreSQL in NestJS applications.\n4: \n5: ## Table of Contents\n6: \n7: - [TypeORM Fundamentals](#typeorm-fundamentals)\n8: - [Entity Patterns](#entity-patterns)\n9: - [Repository Pattern](#repository-pattern)\n10: - [Relationships](#relationships)\n11: - [Migrations](#migrations)\n12: - [Query Optimization](#query-optimization)\n13: - [Transactions](#transactions)\n14: - [Error Handling](#error-handling)\n15: \n16: ---\n17: \n18: ## TypeORM Fundamentals\n19: \n20: ### BaseEntity Pattern\n21: \n22: All entities should extend BaseEntity for automatic timestamps and soft delete:\n23: \n24: ```typescript\n25: // src/core/base/base.entity.ts\n26: import {\n27:     PrimaryGeneratedColumn,\n28:     CreateDateColumn,\n29:     UpdateDateColumn,\n30:     DeleteDateColumn,\n31: } from 'typeorm';\n32: \n33: export abstract class BaseEntity {\n34:     @PrimaryGeneratedColumn('uuid')\n35:     id: string;\n36: \n37:     @CreateDateColumn({ type: 'timestamp' })\n38:     createdAt: Date;\n39: \n40:     @UpdateDateColumn({ type: 'timestamp' })\n41:     updatedAt: Date;\n42: \n43:     @DeleteDateColumn({ type: 'timestamp', nullable: true })\n44:     deletedAt: Date | null;\n45: }\n46: ```\n47: \n48: ### Database Configuration\n49: \n50: ```typescript\n51: // src/config/db.config.ts\n52: import { TypeOrmModuleOptions } from '@nestjs/typeorm';\n53: import { envConfigService } from './env-config.service';\n54: \n55: export const dbConfig: TypeOrmModuleOptions = {\n56:     type: 'postgres',\n57:     host: envConfigService.get('DB_HOST'),\n58:     port: envConfigService.get('DB_PORT'),\n59:     username: envConfigService.get('DB_USERNAME'),\n60:     password: envConfigService.get('DB_PASSWORD'),\n61:     database: envConfigService.get('DB_DATABASE'),\n62:     entities: [__dirname + '/../**/*.entity{.ts,.js}'],\n63:     migrations: [__dirname + '/../database/migrations/*{.ts,.js}'],\n64:     synchronize: false, // NEVER true in production\n65:     logging: envConfigService.get('NODE_ENV') === 'development',\n66:     ssl:\n67:         envConfigService.get('NODE_ENV') === 'production'\n68:             ? {\n69:                   rejectUnauthorized: false,\n70:               }\n71:             : false,\n72: };\n73: ```\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ## Entity Patterns\n78: \n79: ### Basic Entity\n80: \n81: ```typescript\n82: // src/modules/users/user.entity.ts\n83: import { Entity, Column } from 'typeorm';\n84: import { BaseEntity } from 'src/core/base';\n85: \n86: @Entity('users')\n87: export class User extends BaseEntity {\n88:     @Column({ unique: true })\n89:     email: string;\n90: \n91:     @Column()\n92:     name: string;\n93: \n94:     @Column()\n95:     password: string;\n96: \n97:     @Column({ default: true })\n98:     isActive: boolean;\n99: \n100:     @Column('simple-array', { default: [] })\n101:     roles: string[];\n102: }\n103: ```\n104: \n105: ### Column Types\n106: \n107: ```typescript\n108: import { Entity, Column } from 'typeorm';\n109: import { BaseEntity } from 'src/core/base';\n110: \n111: @Entity('products')\n112: export class Product extends BaseEntity {\n113:     // String columns\n114:     @Column({ type: 'varchar', length: 255 })\n115:     name: string;\n116: \n117:     @Column({ type: 'text', nullable: true })\n118:     description: string | null;\n119: \n120:     // Number columns\n121:     @Column({ type: 'decimal', precision: 10, scale: 2 })\n122:     price: number;\n123: \n124:     @Column({ type: 'int', default: 0 })\n125:     stock: number;\n126: \n127:     // Boolean\n128:     @Column({ type: 'boolean', default: true })\n129:     isAvailable: boolean;\n130: \n131:     // Date/Time\n132:     @Column({ type: 'timestamp', nullable: true })\n133:     publishedAt: Date | null;\n134: \n135:     // JSON\n136:     @Column({ type: 'jsonb', nullable: true })\n137:     metadata: Record<string, any> | null;\n138: \n139:     // Array (PostgreSQL)\n140:     @Column('simple-array')\n141:     tags: string[];\n142: \n143:     // Enum (MUST use shared enum from src/shared/enums/, NEVER use varchar for enum columns)\n144:     @Column({\n145:         type: 'enum',\n146:         enum: StatusEnum,\n147:         default: StatusEnum.PENDING,\n148:     })\n149:     status: StatusEnum;\n150: }\n151: ```\n152: \n153: ### Index and Unique Constraints\n154: \n155: ```typescript\n156: import { Entity, Column, Index, Unique } from 'typeorm';\n157: import { BaseEntity } from 'src/core/base';\n158: \n159: @Entity('users')\n160: @Unique(['email'])\n161: @Index(['email', 'isActive']) // Composite index\n162: export class User extends BaseEntity {\n163:     @Column({ unique: true })\n164:     @Index()\n165:     email: string;\n166: \n167:     @Column()\n168:     @Index()\n169:     name: string;\n170: \n171:     @Column()\n172:     password: string;\n173: \n174:     @Column({ default: true })\n175:     isActive: boolean;\n176: }\n177: ```\n178: \n179: ---\n180: \n181: ## Repository Pattern\n182: \n183: ### BaseRepository Implementation\n184: \n185: ```typescript\n186: // src/core/base/base.repository.ts\n187: import {\n188:     Repository,\n189:     FindManyOptions,\n190:     FindOneOptions,\n191:     DeepPartial,\n192: } from 'typeorm';\n193: import { BaseEntity } from './base.entity';\n194: \n195: export abstract class BaseRepository<T extends BaseEntity> {\n196:     constructor(protected readonly repository: Repository<T>) {}\n197: \n198:     async findAll(options?: FindManyOptions<T>): Promise<T[]> {\n199:         return this.repository.find(options);\n200:     }\n201: \n202:     async findById(id: string, relations?: string[]): Promise<T | null> {\n203:         return this.repository.findOne({\n204:             where: { id } as any,\n205:             relations,\n206:         });\n207:     }\n208: \n209:     async findOne(options: FindOneOptions<T>): Promise<T | null> {\n210:         return this.repository.findOne(options);\n211:     }\n212: \n213:     async create(data: DeepPartial<T>): Promise<T> {\n214:         const entity = this.repository.create(data);\n215:         return this.repository.save(entity);\n216:     }\n217: \n218:     async update(id: string, data: DeepPartial<T>): Promise<T | null> {\n219:         await this.repository.update(id, data as any);\n220:         return this.findById(id);\n221:     }\n222: \n223:     async softDelete(id: string): Promise<void> {\n224:         await this.repository.softDelete(id);\n225:     }\n226: \n227:     async delete(id: string): Promise<void> {\n228:         await this.repository.delete(id);\n229:     }\n230: \n231:     async count(options?: FindManyOptions<T>): Promise<number> {\n232:         return this.repository.count(options);\n233:     }\n234: }\n235: ```\n236: \n237: ### Custom Repository\n238: \n239: ```typescript\n240: // src/modules/users/user.repository.ts\n241: import { Injectable } from '@nestjs/common';\n242: import { InjectRepository } from '@nestjs/typeorm';\n243: import { Repository } from 'typeorm';\n244: import { BaseRepository } from 'src/core/base';\n245: import { User } from './user.entity';\n246: \n247: @Injectable()\n248: export class UserRepository extends BaseRepository<User> {\n249:     constructor(\n250:         @InjectRepository(User)\n251:         repository: Repository<User>,\n252:     ) {\n253:         super(repository);\n254:     }\n255: \n256:     // Custom queries\n257:     async findByEmail(email: string): Promise<User | null> {\n258:         return this.repository.findOne({\n259:             where: { email },\n260:         });\n261:     }\n262: \n263:     async findActiveUsers(): Promise<User[]> {\n264:         return this.repository.find({\n265:             where: { isActive: true },\n266:             order: { createdAt: 'DESC' },\n267:         });\n268:     }\n269: \n270:     async findWithRoles(userId: string): Promise<User | null> {\n271:         return this.repository\n272:             .createQueryBuilder('user')\n273:             .where('user.id = :userId', { userId })\n274:             .andWhere(\"'admin' = ANY(user.roles)\")\n275:             .getOne();\n276:     }\n277: \n278:     async searchByName(query: string): Promise<User[]> {\n279:         return this.repository\n280:             .createQueryBuilder('user')\n281:             .where('user.name ILIKE :query', { query: `%${query}%` })\n282:             .andWhere('user.isActive = :isActive', { isActive: true })\n283:             .orderBy('user.name', 'ASC')\n284:             .getMany();\n285:     }\n286: }\n287: ```\n288: \n289: ---\n290: \n291: ## Relationships\n292: \n293: ### One-to-One\n294: \n295: ```typescript\n296: // user.entity.ts\n297: import { Entity, Column, OneToOne, JoinColumn } from 'typeorm';\n298: import { BaseEntity } from 'src/core/base';\n299: import { Profile } from './profile.entity';\n300: \n301: @Entity('users')\n302: export class User extends BaseEntity {\n303:     @Column()\n304:     email: string;\n305: \n306:     @OneToOne(() => Profile, (profile) => profile.user, { cascade: true })\n307:     @JoinColumn()\n308:     profile: Profile;\n309: }\n310: \n311: // profile.entity.ts\n312: @Entity('profiles')\n313: export class Profile extends BaseEntity {\n314:     @Column()\n315:     firstName: string;\n316: \n317:     @Column()\n318:     lastName: string;\n319: \n320:     @OneToOne(() => User, (user) => user.profile)\n321:     user: User;\n322: }\n323: ```\n324: \n325: ### One-to-Many / Many-to-One\n326: \n327: ```typescript\n328: // user.entity.ts\n329: import { Entity, Column, OneToMany } from 'typeorm';\n330: import { BaseEntity } from 'src/core/base';\n331: import { Post } from '../posts/post.entity';\n332: \n333: @Entity('users')\n334: export class User extends BaseEntity {\n335:     @Column()\n336:     name: string;\n337: \n338:     @OneToMany(() => Post, (post) => post.author)\n339:     posts: Post[];\n340: }\n341: \n342: // post.entity.ts\n343: import { Entity, Column, ManyToOne, JoinColumn } from 'typeorm';\n344: import { BaseEntity } from 'src/core/base';\n345: import { User } from '../users/user.entity';\n346: \n347: @Entity('posts')\n348: export class Post extends BaseEntity {\n349:     @Column()\n350:     title: string;\n351: \n352:     @Column('text')\n353:     content: string;\n354: \n355:     @Column()\n356:     authorId: string;\n357: \n358:     @ManyToOne(() => User, (user) => user.posts)\n359:     @JoinColumn({ name: 'authorId' })\n360:     author: User;\n361: }\n362: ```\n363: \n364: ### Many-to-Many\n365: \n366: ```typescript\n367: // user.entity.ts\n368: import { Entity, Column, ManyToMany, JoinTable } from 'typeorm';\n369: import { BaseEntity } from 'src/core/base';\n370: import { Role } from '../roles/role.entity';\n371: \n372: @Entity('users')\n373: export class User extends BaseEntity {\n374:     @Column()\n375:     name: string;\n376: \n377:     @ManyToMany(() => Role, (role) => role.users)\n378:     @JoinTable({\n379:         name: 'user_roles',\n380:         joinColumn: { name: 'userId', referencedColumnName: 'id' },\n381:         inverseJoinColumn: { name: 'roleId', referencedColumnName: 'id' },\n382:     })\n383:     roles: Role[];\n384: }\n385: \n386: // role.entity.ts\n387: @Entity('roles')\n388: export class Role extends BaseEntity {\n389:     @Column({ unique: true })\n390:     name: string;\n391: \n392:     @ManyToMany(() => User, (user) => user.roles)\n393:     users: User[];\n394: }\n395: ```\n396: \n397: ### Loading Relations\n398: \n399: ```typescript\n400: // Eager loading (automatically loads relations)\n401: @Entity('users')\n402: export class User extends BaseEntity {\n403:     @OneToOne(() => Profile, (profile) => profile.user, { eager: true })\n404:     @JoinColumn()\n405:     profile: Profile;\n406: }\n407: \n408: // Lazy loading\n409: const user = await userRepository.findOne({\n410:     where: { id },\n411:     relations: ['profile', 'posts'],\n412: });\n413: \n414: // With QueryBuilder\n415: const user = await userRepository\n416:     .createQueryBuilder('user')\n417:     .leftJoinAndSelect('user.profile', 'profile')\n418:     .leftJoinAndSelect('user.posts', 'posts')\n419:     .where('user.id = :id', { id })\n420:     .getOne();\n421: \n422: // Nested relations\n423: const user = await userRepository.findOne({\n424:     where: { id },\n425:     relations: {\n426:         profile: true,\n427:         posts: {\n428:             comments: true,\n429:         },\n430:     },\n431: });\n432: ```\n433: \n434: ---\n435: \n436: ## Migrations\n437: \n438: ### Generate Migration\n439: \n440: ```bash\n441: # Generate migration from entity changes\n442: npm run migration:generate -- src/database/migrations/CreateUserTable\n443: \n444: # Create empty migration\n445: npm run migration:create -- src/database/migrations/AddIndexToUser\n446: ```\n447: \n448: ### Migration File\n449: \n450: ```typescript\n451: // src/database/migrations/1234567890-CreateUserTable.ts\n452: import { MigrationInterface, QueryRunner, Table } from 'typeorm';\n453: \n454: export class CreateUserTable1234567890 implements MigrationInterface {\n455:     public async up(queryRunner: QueryRunner): Promise<void> {\n456:         await queryRunner.createTable(\n457:             new Table({\n458:                 name: 'users',\n459:                 columns: [\n460:                     {\n461:                         name: 'id',\n462:                         type: 'uuid',\n463:                         isPrimary: true,\n464:                         generationStrategy: 'uuid',\n465:                         default: 'uuid_generate_v4()',\n466:                     },\n467:                     {\n468:                         name: 'email',\n469:                         type: 'varchar',\n470:                         length: '255',\n471:                         isUnique: true,\n472:                     },\n473:                     {\n474:                         name: 'name',\n475:                         type: 'varchar',\n476:                         length: '255',\n477:                     },\n478:                     {\n479:                         name: 'password',\n480:                         type: 'varchar',\n481:                         length: '255',\n482:                     },\n483:                     {\n484:                         name: 'isActive',\n485:                         type: 'boolean',\n486:                         default: true,\n487:                     },\n488:                     {\n489:                         name: 'roles',\n490:                         type: 'text',\n491:                         isArray: true,\n492:                         default: 'ARRAY[]::text[]',\n493:                     },\n494:                     {\n495:                         name: 'createdAt',\n496:                         type: 'timestamp',\n497:                         default: 'now()',\n498:                     },\n499:                     {\n500:                         name: 'updatedAt',\n501:                         type: 'timestamp',\n502:                         default: 'now()',\n503:                     },\n504:                     {\n505:                         name: 'deletedAt',\n506:                         type: 'timestamp',\n507:                         isNullable: true,\n508:                     },\n509:                 ],\n510:                 indices: [\n511:                     {\n512:                         name: 'IDX_USER_EMAIL',\n513:                         columnNames: ['email'],\n514:                     },\n515:                 ],\n516:             }),\n517:             true,\n518:         );\n519:     }\n520: \n521:     public async down(queryRunner: QueryRunner): Promise<void> {\n522:         await queryRunner.dropTable('users');\n523:     }\n524: }\n525: ```\n526: \n527: ### Run Migrations\n528: \n529: ```bash\n530: # Run all pending migrations\n531: npm run migration:run\n532: \n533: # Revert last migration\n534: npm run migration:revert\n535: \n536: # Show migration status\n537: npm run migration:show\n538: ```\n539: \n540: ---\n541: \n542: ## Query Optimization\n543: \n544: ### Select Specific Fields\n545: \n546: ```typescript\n547: // ❌ Fetches all fields\n548: const users = await userRepository.find();\n549: \n550: // ✅ Only fetch needed fields\n551: const users = await userRepository.find({\n552:     select: ['id', 'email', 'name'],\n553: });\n554: \n555: // With QueryBuilder\n556: const users = await userRepository\n557:     .createQueryBuilder('user')\n558:     .select(['user.id', 'user.email', 'user.name'])\n559:     .getMany();\n560: ```\n561: \n562: ### Pagination\n563: \n564: ```typescript\n565: async findPaginated(page: number = 1, limit: number = 10): Promise<[User[], number]> {\n566:     const skip = (page - 1) * limit;\n567: \n568:     return this.repository.findAndCount({\n569:         skip,\n570:         take: limit,\n571:         order: { createdAt: 'DESC' },\n572:     });\n573: }\n574: \n575: // With QueryBuilder\n576: async findPaginatedWithSearch(\n577:     page: number,\n578:     limit: number,\n579:     search?: string,\n580: ): Promise<[User[], number]> {\n581:     const query = this.repository\n582:         .createQueryBuilder('user')\n583:         .skip((page - 1) * limit)\n584:         .take(limit)\n585:         .orderBy('user.createdAt', 'DESC');\n586: \n587:     if (search) {\n588:         query.where('user.name ILIKE :search', { search: `%${search}%` });\n589:     }\n590: \n591:     return query.getManyAndCount();\n592: }\n593: ```\n594: \n595: ### N+1 Query Prevention\n596: \n597: ```typescript\n598: // ❌ N+1 Problem\n599: const users = await userRepository.find();\n600: for (const user of users) {\n601:     user.posts = await postRepository.find({ where: { authorId: user.id } });\n602: }\n603: \n604: // ✅ Solution: Use relations\n605: const users = await userRepository.find({\n606:     relations: ['posts'],\n607: });\n608: \n609: // ✅ Or use QueryBuilder with join\n610: const users = await userRepository\n611:     .createQueryBuilder('user')\n612:     .leftJoinAndSelect('user.posts', 'post')\n613:     .getMany();\n614: ```\n615: \n616: ### Indexes\n617: \n618: ```typescript\n619: // Add indexes for frequently queried fields\n620: @Entity('users')\n621: @Index(['email', 'isActive']) // Composite index\n622: export class User extends BaseEntity {\n623:     @Column({ unique: true })\n624:     @Index() // Single field index\n625:     email: string;\n626: \n627:     @Column()\n628:     @Index()\n629:     name: string;\n630: \n631:     @Column({ default: true })\n632:     isActive: boolean;\n633: }\n634: ```\n635: \n636: ---\n637: \n638: ## Transactions\n639: \n640: ### Simple Transaction\n641: \n642: ```typescript\n643: import { DataSource } from 'typeorm';\n644: \n645: @Injectable()\n646: export class UserService {\n647:     constructor(private dataSource: DataSource) {}\n648: \n649:     async createUserWithProfile(userData: CreateUserDto): Promise<User> {\n650:         const queryRunner = this.dataSource.createQueryRunner();\n651:         await queryRunner.connect();\n652:         await queryRunner.startTransaction();\n653: \n654:         try {\n655:             // Create user\n656:             const user = queryRunner.manager.create(User, userData);\n657:             await queryRunner.manager.save(user);\n658: \n659:             // Create profile\n660:             const profile = queryRunner.manager.create(Profile, {\n661:                 userId: user.id,\n662:                 firstName: userData.firstName,\n663:                 lastName: userData.lastName,\n664:             });\n665:             await queryRunner.manager.save(profile);\n666: \n667:             // Commit transaction\n668:             await queryRunner.commitTransaction();\n669:             return user;\n670:         } catch (error) {\n671:             // Rollback on error\n672:             await queryRunner.rollbackTransaction();\n673:             throw error;\n674:         } finally {\n675:             // Release query runner\n676:             await queryRunner.release();\n677:         }\n678:     }\n679: }\n680: ```\n681: \n682: ### Transaction with DataSource\n683: \n684: ```typescript\n685: async transferFunds(fromId: string, toId: string, amount: number): Promise<void> {\n686:     await this.dataSource.transaction(async (manager) => {\n687:         // Deduct from sender\n688:         await manager.decrement(\n689:             Account,\n690:             { id: fromId },\n691:             'balance',\n692:             amount,\n693:         );\n694: \n695:         // Add to receiver\n696:         await manager.increment(\n697:             Account,\n698:             { id: toId },\n699:             'balance',\n700:             amount,\n701:         );\n702: \n703:         // Create transfer record\n704:         await manager.save(TransferLog, {\n705:             fromId,\n706:             toId,\n707:             amount,\n708:         });\n709:     });\n710: }\n711: ```\n712: \n713: ---\n714: \n715: ## Error Handling\n716: \n717: ### TypeORM Errors\n718: \n719: ```typescript\n720: import { QueryFailedError } from 'typeorm';\n721: import { ConflictException, NotFoundException, BadRequestException } from '@nestjs/common';\n722: \n723: async createUser(data: CreateUserDto): Promise<User> {\n724:     try {\n725:         return await this.repository.create(data);\n726:     } catch (error) {\n727:         if (error instanceof QueryFailedError) {\n728:             // Unique constraint violation\n729:             if (error.message.includes('duplicate key')) {\n730:                 throw new ConflictException('Email already exists');\n731:             }\n732: \n733:             // Foreign key constraint\n734:             if (error.message.includes('foreign key constraint')) {\n735:                 throw new BadRequestException('Invalid reference');\n736:             }\n737: \n738:             // Not null constraint\n739:             if (error.message.includes('not-null constraint')) {\n740:                 throw new BadRequestException('Required field missing');\n741:             }\n742:         }\n743: \n744:         throw error;\n745:     }\n746: }\n747: ```\n748: \n749: ### Custom Error Handler\n750: \n751: ```typescript\n752: @Injectable()\n753: export class DatabaseErrorHandler {\n754:     handleError(error: unknown): never {\n755:         if (error instanceof QueryFailedError) {\n756:             const message = error.message.toLowerCase();\n757: \n758:             if (message.includes('duplicate key')) {\n759:                 throw new ConflictException('Resource already exists');\n760:             }\n761: \n762:             if (message.includes('foreign key')) {\n763:                 throw new BadRequestException('Invalid reference');\n764:             }\n765: \n766:             if (message.includes('not-null')) {\n767:                 throw new BadRequestException('Required field missing');\n768:             }\n769:         }\n770: \n771:         throw new InternalServerErrorException('Database operation failed');\n772:     }\n773: }\n774: ```\n775: \n776: ---\n777: \n778: ## Best Practices Summary\n779: \n780: ### ✅ DO:\n781: \n782: - Extend BaseEntity for all entities\n783: - Use migrations for schema changes (never synchronize in production)\n784: - Add indexes on frequently queried fields\n785: - Use transactions for multi-step operations\n786: - Select only needed fields\n787: - Use relations to prevent N+1 queries\n788: - Use QueryBuilder for complex queries\n789: - Handle database errors properly\n790: - Use soft delete for important data\n791: - Add unique constraints where needed\n792: \n793: ### ❌ DON'T:\n794: \n795: - Use synchronize: true in production\n796: - Forget to add indexes on foreign keys\n797: - Load unnecessary relations\n798: - Skip transactions for multi-step operations\n799: - Expose raw database errors to users\n800: - Use SELECT \\* in queries\n801: - Hard delete without consideration\n802: - Forget to release query runners\n803: - Use eager loading everywhere\n804: - Skip migration testing\n805: \n806: ---\n807: \n808: **Related Files:**\n809: \n810: - [SKILL.md](../SKILL.md) - Main guide\n811: - [services-and-repositories.md](services-and-repositories.md) - Service/Repository patterns\n812: - [architecture-overview.md](architecture-overview.md) - Four-layer architecture\n813: - [validation-patterns.md](validation-patterns.md) - Entity validation\n\n(End of file - total 813 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Database Patterns - TypeORM in NestJS\n\nComplete guide to database access patterns using TypeORM with PostgreSQL in NestJS applications.\n\n## Table of Contents\n\n- [TypeORM Fundamentals](#typeorm-fundamentals)\n- [Entity Patterns](#entity-patterns)\n- [Repository Pattern](#repository-pattern)\n- [Relationships](#relationships)\n- [Migrations](#migrations)\n- [Query Optimization](#query-optimization)\n- [Transactions](#transactions)\n- [Error Handling](#error-handling)\n\n---\n\n## TypeORM Fundamentals\n\n### BaseEntity Pattern","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude/nestjs/guides/database-patterns.md","time":{"start":1779167868947,"end":1779167869256}},"id":"prt_e3eab3352001J0aC2lHiJebuJL","sessionID":"ses_1c15753b5ffe0uF0tU9Lf0PCIg","messageID":"msg_e3eab1fed00113CRmmJPq6bE3e"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779167871105,"sessionID":"ses_1c15753b5ffe0uF0tU9Lf0PCIg","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_01_Zqh9Hf7nI2cOyNyrNw4M8684","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/nestjs/templates/core/base/base.entity.ts"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/nestjs/templates/core/base/base.entity.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: import {\n2:     PrimaryGeneratedColumn,\n3:     CreateDateColumn,\n4:     UpdateDateColumn,\n5:     DeleteDateColumn,\n6: } from 'typeorm';\n7: \n8: export abstract class BaseEntity {\n9:     @PrimaryGeneratedColumn('uuid')\n10:     id: string;\n11: \n12:     @CreateDateColumn({ name: 'created_at', type: 'timestamp' })\n13:     createdAt: Date;\n14: \n15:     @UpdateDateColumn({ name: 'updated_at', type: 'timestamp' })\n16:     updatedAt: Date;\n17: \n18:     @DeleteDateColumn({ name: 'deleted_at', type: 'timestamp', nullable: true })\n19:     deletedAt: Date | null;\n20: }\n\n(End of file - total 20 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"import {\n    PrimaryGeneratedColumn,\n    CreateDateColumn,\n    UpdateDateColumn,\n    DeleteDateColumn,\n} from 'typeorm';\n\nexport abstract class BaseEntity {\n    @PrimaryGeneratedColumn('uuid')\n    id: string;\n\n    @CreateDateColumn({ name: 'created_at', type: 'timestamp' })\n    createdAt: Date;\n\n    @UpdateDateColumn({ name: 'updated_at', type: 'timestamp' })\n    updatedAt: Date;\n\n    @DeleteDateColumn({ name: 'deleted_at', type: 'timestamp', nullable: true })\n    deletedAt: Date | null;\n}","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude/nestjs/templates/core/base/base.entity.ts","time":{"start":1779167870667,"end":1779167871103}},"id":"prt_e3eab397d001IZfrbnY1NMyyiS","sessionID":"ses_1c15753b5ffe0uF0tU9Lf0PCIg","messageID":"msg_e3eab1fed00113CRmmJPq6bE3e"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1779167871375,"sessionID":"ses_1c15753b5ffe0uF0tU9Lf0PCIg","part":{"id":"prt_e3eab418e001LZBtOpEAfdJPLT","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"785cbc61bdf517a8f4706995a67c7259dcdacb25","messageID":"msg_e3eab1fed00113CRmmJPq6bE3e","sessionID":"ses_1c15753b5ffe0uF0tU9Lf0PCIg","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":33117,"input":13642,"output":125,"reasoning":22,"cache":{"write":0,"read":19328}},"cost":0.024528896}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1779167873038,"sessionID":"ses_1c15753b5ffe0uF0tU9Lf0PCIg","part":{"id":"prt_e3eab480b001REVEScoVLsl7qt","messageID":"msg_e3eab41d0001hMh9CR2xJ6RR46","sessionID":"ses_1c15753b5ffe0uF0tU9Lf0PCIg","snapshot":"5b32d193c8016c1a67ecec154273117a2f62e809","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779168062571,"sessionID":"ses_1c15753b5ffe0uF0tU9Lf0PCIg","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_00_hoCgaZ64p17nY341L1vF6637","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude-project/nestfind/docs/PROJECT_DATABASE.md","content":"# PROJECT_DATABASE\n\n## Schema Overview\n\nAll entities extend `BaseEntity` which provides:\n- `id` — UUID primary key\n- `createdAt` — `timestamp` (auto-managed)\n- `updatedAt` — `timestamp` (auto-managed)\n- `deletedAt` — `timestamp | null` (soft delete support)\n\nColumn naming convention: `snake_case` in the database (`@CreateDateColumn({ name: 'created_at' })`).\n\n---\n\n## Entities\n\n### User\n\nRepresents all registered users (Renters and Admins). Extends `BaseEntity` with soft delete.\n\n**Table:** `users`\n\n| Field | Type | Constraints | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|-------------|\n| `id` | `uuid` | PK, default: `uuid_generate_v4()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n| `name` | `varchar(100)` | NOT NULL | User's full name |\n| `email` | `varchar(255)` | UNIQUE, NOT NULL | Login email address |\n| `password` | `varchar(255)` | NOT NULL | bcrypt-hashed password |\n| `phone` | `varchar(20)` | NULLABLE | Optional phone number |\n| `role` | `enum` (`RoleEnum`) | NOT NULL, default: `'renter'` | `renter` \\| `admin` |\n| `status` | `enum` (`UserStatusEnum`) | NOT NULL, default: `'active'` | `active` \\| `suspended` |\n| `email_verified_at` | `timestamp` | NULLABLE | Null until email verification completes |\n| `created_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n| `updated_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n| `deleted_at` | `timestamp` | NULLABLE | Soft delete timestamp |\n\n**Indexes:**\n- `UNIQUE` on `email`\n- `INDEX` on `role`\n- `INDEX` on `status`\n- `INDEX` on `(role, status)` composite\n\n**Relationships:**\n- `hasMany` → `RefreshToken` (one user has many refresh tokens)\n- `hasMany` → `PasswordResetToken` (one user has many reset tokens)\n- `hasMany` → `Favorite` (one user has many favorites)\n- `hasMany` → `Inquiry` (one user submits many inquiries)\n\n---\n\n### RefreshToken\n\nStores JWT refresh tokens for rotation and invalidation. Each refresh creates a new row; the old row is marked deleted when rotated. Not extending `BaseEntity` (no need for update timestamps or soft delete — expiries handle lifecycle).\n\n**Table:** `refresh_tokens`\n\n| Field | Type | Constraints | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|-------------|\n| `id` | `uuid` | PK, default: `uuid_generate_v4()` | Primary key |\n| `user_id` | `uuid` | FK → `users.id`, NOT NULL, ON DELETE CASCADE | Owning user |\n| `token` | `varchar(500)` | NOT NULL, UNIQUE | Encoded JWT refresh token string |\n| `expires_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL | Token expiration time (7 days from issue) |\n| `revoked_at` | `timestamp` | NULLABLE | Set when token is rotated or user logs out |\n| `created_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Token creation time |\n\n**Indexes:**\n- `UNIQUE` on `token`\n- `INDEX` on `user_id`\n- `INDEX` on `expires_at`\n\n**Relationships:**\n- `belongsTo` → `User` via `user_id`\n\n---\n\n### PasswordResetToken\n\nStores tokens for the forgot-password / reset-password flow. Tokens expire after a configurable window (e.g., 1 hour).\n\n**Table:** `password_reset_tokens`\n\n| Field | Type | Constraints | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|-------------|\n| `id` | `uuid` | PK, default: `uuid_generate_v4()` | Primary key |\n| `user_id` | `uuid` | FK → `users.id`, NOT NULL, ON DELETE CASCADE | Owning user |\n| `token` | `varchar(500)` | NOT NULL, UNIQUE | Secure random reset token |\n| `expires_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL | Token expiry (e.g., 1 hour from creation) |\n| `used_at` | `timestamp` | NULLABLE | Set when password is successfully reset |\n| `created_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Token creation time |\n\n**Indexes:**\n- `UNIQUE` on `token`\n- `INDEX` on `user_id`\n\n**Relationships:**\n- `belongsTo` → `User` via `user_id`\n\n---\n\n### Property\n\nRepresents a rental property listing. Supports soft delete (archiving). Address fields are stored as individual columns for search/indexing; API layer nests them into an `address` object.\n\n**Table:** `properties`\n\n| Field | Type | Constraints | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|-------------|\n| `id` | `uuid` | PK, default: `uuid_generate_v4()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n| `title` | `varchar(200)` | NOT NULL | Listing title (5–200 chars) |\n| `description` | `text` | NOT NULL | Full description (20–5000 chars) |\n| `price` | `decimal(10,2)` | NOT NULL | Monthly rent (> 0) |\n| `bedrooms` | `integer` | NOT NULL, CHECK (≥ 0) | Number of bedrooms |\n| `bathrooms` | `integer` | NOT NULL, CHECK (≥ 0) | Number of bathrooms |\n| `square_feet` | `integer` | NULLABLE, CHECK (> 0) | Living area in square feet |\n| `property_type` | `enum` (`PropertyTypeEnum`) | NOT NULL | `apartment` \\| `house` \\| `condo` \\| `townhouse` \\| `studio` |\n| `address_street` | `varchar(200)` | NOT NULL | Street address |\n| `address_city` | `varchar(100)` | NOT NULL | City |\n| `address_state` | `varchar(100)` | NOT NULL | State / province |\n| `address_zip_code` | `varchar(10)` | NOT NULL | ZIP / postal code |\n| `address_latitude` | `decimal(10,7)` | NULLABLE | Geocoordinate latitude (-90 to 90) |\n| `address_longitude` | `decimal(10,7)` | NULLABLE | Geocoordinate longitude (-180 to 180) |\n| `available_from` | `date` | NULLABLE | Date property becomes available |\n| `created_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n| `updated_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n| `deleted_at` | `timestamp` | NULLABLE | Soft delete / archive timestamp |\n\n**Indexes:**\n- `INDEX` on `property_type`\n- `INDEX` on `price`\n- `INDEX` on `bedrooms`\n- `INDEX` on `bathrooms`\n- `INDEX` on `address_city`\n- `INDEX` on `address_state`\n- `INDEX` on `(address_latitude, address_longitude)` — geospatial queries\n- `GIN INDEX` or `tsvector` on `title || ' ' || description || ' ' || address_city || ' ' || address_state` for full-text search (optional, for performance at scale)\n\n**Relationships:**\n- `hasMany` → `PropertyPhoto` (one property has many photos)\n- `belongsToMany` → `Amenity` via `property_amenities` junction\n- `hasMany` → `Favorite` (one property is favorited by many users)\n- `hasMany` → `Inquiry` (one property receives many inquiries)\n\n---\n\n### PropertyPhoto\n\nStores uploaded photos for a property. Multiple photos per property with ordering and a primary photo designation.\n\n**Table:** `property_photos`\n\n| Field | Type | Constraints | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|-------------|\n| `id` | `uuid` | PK, default: `uuid_generate_v4()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n| `property_id` | `uuid` | FK → `properties.id`, NOT NULL, ON DELETE CASCADE | Owning property |\n| `url` | `varchar(500)` | NOT NULL | Photo URL (S3 / CDN path) |\n| `is_primary` | `boolean` | NOT NULL, default: `false` | Whether this is the main/thumbnail photo |\n| `sort_order` | `integer` | NOT NULL, default: `0` | Display order in gallery |\n| `created_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n| `updated_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n\n**Indexes:**\n- `INDEX` on `property_id`\n- `INDEX` on `(property_id, sort_order)`\n\n**Business Rule:** Only one photo per property may have `is_primary = true`. Enforced at the application layer.\n\n**Relationships:**\n- `belongsTo` → `Property` via `property_id`\n\n---\n\n### Amenity\n\nPredefined list of amenities that can be associated with properties. Managed by admins.\n\n**Table:** `amenities`\n\n| Field | Type | Constraints | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|-------------|\n| `id` | `uuid` | PK, default: `uuid_generate_v4()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n| `name` | `varchar(50)` | UNIQUE, NOT NULL | Amenity name (e.g., \"parking\", \"gym\") |\n| `icon` | `varchar(50)` | NOT NULL | Icon identifier for frontend rendering |\n| `created_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n| `updated_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n| `deleted_at` | `timestamp` | NULLABLE | Soft delete |\n\n**Indexes:**\n- `UNIQUE` on `name`\n\n**Relationships:**\n- `belongsToMany` → `Property` via `property_amenities` junction\n\n---\n\n### PropertyAmenity\n\nJunction table for the many-to-many relationship between `Property` and `Amenity`. Each row links one property to one amenity.\n\n**Table:** `property_amenities`\n\n| Field | Type | Constraints | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|-------------|\n| `property_id` | `uuid` | PK (composite), FK → `properties.id`, NOT NULL, ON DELETE CASCADE | Property reference |\n| `amenity_id` | `uuid` | PK (composite), FK → `amenities.id`, NOT NULL, ON DELETE CASCADE | Amenity reference |\n\n**Primary Key:** Composite `(property_id, amenity_id)`\n\n**Indexes:**\n- `INDEX` on `amenity_id`\n\n**Relationships:**\n- `belongsTo` → `Property` via `property_id`\n- `belongsTo` → `Amenity` via `amenity_id`\n\n---\n\n### Favorite\n\nRepresents a renter saving a property to their favorites. Idempotent — adding a duplicate returns the existing record (API handles this). Composite unique constraint prevents duplicates.\n\n**Table:** `favorites`\n\n| Field | Type | Constraints | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|-------------|\n| `id` | `uuid` | PK, default: `uuid_generate_v4()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n| `user_id` | `uuid` | FK → `users.id`, NOT NULL, ON DELETE CASCADE | The renter who favorited |\n| `property_id` | `uuid` | FK → `properties.id`, NOT NULL, ON DELETE CASCADE | The favorited property |\n| `created_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n\n**Indexes:**\n- `UNIQUE` on `(user_id, property_id)` — prevents duplicate favorites\n- `INDEX` on `user_id`\n- `INDEX` on `property_id`\n\n**Relationships:**\n- `belongsTo` → `User` via `user_id`\n- `belongsTo` → `Property` via `property_id`\n\n---\n\n### Inquiry\n\nRepresents a contact/inquiry submission from a renter about a specific property. Admins manage inquiry status and responses.\n\n**Table:** `inquiries`\n\n| Field | Type | Constraints | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|-------------|\n| `id` | `uuid` | PK, default: `uuid_generate_v4()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n| `property_id` | `uuid` | FK → `properties.id`, NOT NULL, ON DELETE SET NULL | Subject property |\n| `user_id` | `uuid` | FK → `users.id`, NOT NULL, ON DELETE SET NULL | Submitting renter |\n| `name` | `varchar(100)` | NOT NULL | Submitter's name (denormalized for display) |\n| `email` | `varchar(255)` | NOT NULL | Submitter's email (denormalized) |\n| `phone` | `varchar(20)` | NULLABLE | Submitter's phone (denormalized) |\n| `message` | `text` | NOT NULL | Inquiry message body (10–2000 chars) |\n| `status` | `enum` (`InquiryStatusEnum`) | NOT NULL, default: `'new'` | `new` \\| `read` \\| `responded` |\n| `response` | `text` | NULLABLE | Admin's response text |\n| `responded_at` | `timestamp` | NULLABLE | Set when admin responds |\n| `created_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n| `updated_at` | `timestamp` | NOT NULL, default: `now()` | Inherited from BaseEntity |\n\n**Note:** `name`, `email`, `phone` are denormalized from the `User` record at submission time. This preserves the inquiry even if the user account is later deleted (hence `ON DELETE SET NULL` on `user_id`).\n\n**Indexes:**\n- `INDEX` on `property_id`\n- `INDEX` on `user_id`\n- `INDEX` on `status`\n- `INDEX` on `(status, created_at)` — for admin dashboard filtering\n\n**Relationships:**\n- `belongsTo` → `Property` via `property_id`\n- `belongsTo` → `User` via `user_id`\n\n---\n\n## Enums\n\n### RoleEnum\n\nUsed in `users.role`.\n\n| Value | Description |\n|-------|-------------|\n| `renter` | Standard user who browses and saves properties, submits inquiries |\n| `admin` | Administrator with full system access |\n\n---\n\n### UserStatusEnum\n\nUsed in `users.status`.\n\n| Value | Description |\n|-------|-------------|\n| `active` | Account in good standing |\n| `suspended` | Account suspended by admin; cannot log in |\n\n---\n\n### PropertyTypeEnum\n\nUsed in `properties.property_type`.\n\n| Value | Description |\n|-------|-------------|\n| `apartment` | Apartment unit |\n| `house` | Single-family house |\n| `condo` | Condominium |\n| `townhouse` | Townhouse |\n| `studio` | Studio apartment |\n\n---\n\n### InquiryStatusEnum\n\nUsed in `inquiries.status`.\n\n| Value | Description |\n|-------|-------------|\n| `new` | Unread inquiry (default on submission) |\n| `read` | Viewed by admin |\n| `responded` | Admin has sent a response |\n\n---\n\n## Relationships\n\n### Entity Relationship Diagram\n\n```\nusers (1) ────────< (many) refresh_tokens\nusers (1) ────────< (many) password_reset_tokens\nusers (1) ────────< (many) favorites\nusers (1) ────────< (many) inquiries\n\nproperties (1) ───< (many) property_photos\nproperties (1) ───< (many) favorites\nproperties (1) ───< (many) inquiries\nproperties (many) >────< (many) amenities  [via property_amenities]\n```\n\n### Foreign Key Summary\n\n| Child Table | FK Column | Parent Table | On Delete |\n|-------------|----------|--------------|-----------|\n| `refresh_tokens` | `user_id` | `users.id` | CASCADE |\n| `password_reset_tokens` | `user_id` | `users.id` | CASCADE |\n| `property_photos` | `property_id` | `properties.id` | CASCADE |\n| `property_amenities` | `property_id` | `properties.id` | CASCADE |\n| `property_amenities` | `amenity_id` | `amenities.id` | CASCADE |\n| `favorites` | `user_id` | `users.id` | CASCADE |\n| `favorites` | `property_id` | `properties.id` | CASCADE |\n| `inquiries` | `property_id` | `properties.id` | SET NULL |\n| `inquiries` | `user_id` | `users.id` | SET NULL |\n\n### Relationship Details\n\n| Relationship | Type | Owner | Inverse | Junction |\n|-------------|------|-------|---------|----------|\n| User → RefreshToken | One-to-Many | — | RefreshToken.user ↔ User.refreshTokens | — |\n| User → PasswordResetToken | One-to-Many | — | PasswordResetToken.user ↔ User.resetTokens | — |\n| User → Favorite | One-to-Many | — | Favorite.user ↔ User.favorites | — |\n| User → Inquiry | One-to-Many | — | Inquiry.user ↔ User.inquiries | — |\n| Property → PropertyPhoto | One-to-Many | — | PropertyPhoto.property ↔ Property.photos | — |\n| Property → Favorite | One-to-Many | — | Favorite.property ↔ Property.favorites | — |\n| Property → Inquiry | One-to-Many | — | Inquiry.property ↔ Property.inquiries | — |\n| Property ↔ Amenity | Many-to-Many | Property (JoinTable) | Property.amenities ↔ Amenity.properties | `property_amenities` |\n\n---\n\n## Conventions\n\n### Timestamps\n- All `timestamp` columns use `default: now()` for `created_at`.\n- `updated_at` is auto-managed by TypeORM (`@UpdateDateColumn`).\n- `deleted_at` is managed by TypeORM soft-delete (`@DeleteDateColumn`).\n\n### Soft Delete\n- Enabled on: `users`, `properties`, `amenities`.\n- NOT enabled on: `refresh_tokens` (managed via `revoked_at` + `expires_at`), `password_reset_tokens` (managed via `expires_at` + `used_at`), `favorites` (hard delete on unfavorite), `inquiries` (retained indefinitely for audit), `property_photos` (hard delete on removal), `property_amenities` (junction – hard delete on unlink).\n\n### Naming\n- **Tables**: `snake_case` plural (e.g., `property_photos`, `password_reset_tokens`)\n- **Columns**: `snake_case` (e.g., `user_id`, `property_type`, `address_city`)\n- **Enums**: PascalCase suffix `Enum` in TypeScript (e.g., `RoleEnum`, `PropertyTypeEnum`)\n\n### Data Types\n- Monetary values: `decimal(10,2)` (supports prices up to $99,999,999.99)\n- Geo-coordinates: `decimal(10,7)` (sub-meter precision)\n- Percentages/ratios: `decimal(5,2)` if needed in future\n\n---\n\n*Generated: 2026-05-19 | Source: PROJECT_KNOWLEDGE.md + PROJECT_API.md + database-patterns.md*\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude-project/nestfind/docs/PROJECT_DATABASE.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":".claude-project/nestfind/docs/PROJECT_DATABASE.md","time":{"start":1779168062234,"end":1779168062568}},"id":"prt_e3eac0598001kE1wiFbeDnH8Ht","sessionID":"ses_1c15753b5ffe0uF0tU9Lf0PCIg","messageID":"msg_e3eab41d0001hMh9CR2xJ6RR46"}}
